speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for War (1) whether lie is aware that the Essex Yeomanry have been ordered to wear blue on the

Coronation parade; that green is their normal colour, and that many of their men have already purchased green privately; and whether, as the issue of rifle-regiment green, which is suitable to them, would add no extra burden to the State, he will change the orders to meet their wishes;

(2) whether he is aware that officers of the Essex Yeomanry are only in possession of a green undress uniform; and who will pay for the blue one if they are ordered to wear blue on the Coronation parade?
